HEADWORD: Mahound
<hw>Ma`hound</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A contemptuous name
for Mohammed; hence, an evil spirit; a devil.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who's this, my <qex>mahound</qex> cousin ?</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mahout</ent>⟦br⟧
